The paper focuses on open-ended video question answering, which involves natural language processing and computer vision. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the paper proposes a hierarchical convolutional self-attention encoder-decoder network, which involves deep learning and neural networks, making cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) another likely sub-category. The paper also involves artificial intelligence and machine learning techniques, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) a possible sub-category. The paper also involves extensive experiments and evaluation, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another possible sub-category. Finally, the paper involves multi-modal processing of video data, making cs.MM (Multimedia) a possible sub-category.
